Definition: a sect of Orthodox Jews that arose out of a pietistic movement originating in eastern Europe in the second half of the 18th century
Example: a sect that follows the Mosaic law strictly
Synonyms: Hassidim, Hasidism, Chasidim, Chassidim, Orthodox_Judaism, a, sect, of, Orthodox, Jews, that, arose, out, pietistic, movement, originating, in, eastern, Europe, the, second, half, th, century, follows, Mosaic, law, strictly
Category: noun.group
